# ============================================================
#  HEADLAMP — .gitignore
#
#  This repo uses a WHITELIST strategy: everything is ignored
#  by default, and only headlamp.html is explicitly allowed.
#
#  WHY ONLY headlamp.html?
#    The built file is the app. It is fully self-contained —
#    all Bible data, recommendations, and code are embedded.
#    Source files (app_template.html, build.py, fetch_*.py,
#    gospel_stories.json, etc.) contain no user-facing logic
#    that isn't already in the built output, and the fetch
#    scripts require API keys that should never be shared.
#
#  WHAT IS KEPT OUT:
#    .env                  — your API keys. NEVER commit.
#    app_template.html     — source template (build input)
#    build.py / fetch_*.py — build + fetch scripts
#    *.json (data files)   — large build-time data
#    .gemini_cache/        — Gemini API response cache
#    .esv_cache/           — ESV API response cache
#    bible-data/           — raw per-book JSON source files
#    bible-data.worktrees/ — Copilot worktree artefact
#    __pycache__ / *.pyc   — Python bytecode
#    .DS_Store             — macOS Finder metadata
#
#  GITHUB PAGES:
#    headlamp.html will be served at:
#      https://<you>.github.io/headlamp/headlamp.html
#    To serve it at the root URL, also commit an index.html
#    that redirects:  <meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0;url=headlamp.html">
# ============================================================

# Ignore everything by default
*

# Un-ignore only what belongs in the repo
!.gitignore
!headlamp.html
!index.html
